article.headline: Detroit 88, N. Michigan 53
article.story: DETROIT -- Doug Anderson scored 25 points and Ray McCallum added 22 on Friday night as Detroit opened its season with an 88-53 victory over Northern Michigan. Anderson also was a big factor on the boards and on defense, coming up with nine rebounds and five steals. McCallum's effort included six assists and five rebounds. Detroit also was effective from 3-point range, converting 11 shots from beyond the arc. Northern Michigan's shooting touch was off most of the night, hitting just a third of its shots from the field. T.J. Cameron scored 20 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Northern Michigan.
